      "date": "2013-11-08 21:48:52.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nJinshan, if I understand correctly (?), the issue is that osc_dec_unstable_pages _may_ be called twice via brw_commit. I think this patch will work, but it seems hard to follow and understand. Can you have a look at this:\n\n    http://review.whamcloud.com/8219\n\nI tried to fix the same issue as this patch, but in a more understandable way. What do you think?",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "40805194718b16ff714d848dad583f54b0add05f",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 4,
        "name": "Jinshan Xiong",
        "email": "jinshan.xiong@intel.com",
        "username": "Jay",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2013-11-08 22:22:53.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\n\"Jinshan, if I understand correctly (?), the issue is that osc_dec_unstable_pages _may_ be called twice via brw_commit. I think this patch will work, but it seems hard to follow and understand. Can you have a look at this:\"\n\nthey're quite similar. The problem with your patch is that it calls dec/inc_unstable_pages() inside the spin lock, this is really not good.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
